    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`NVIM v0.13.0-dev-680` 7bf2ab4b87e\n\n```\nThread 0 Crashed::  Dispatch queue: com.apple.main-thread\n0   nvim                          \t       0x1026e628c ins_compl_next + 5904\n1   nvim                          \t       0x1026edf44 ins_complete + 5988\n2   nvim                          \t       0x1026dfbfc ins_compl_new_leader + 580\n3   nvim                          \t       0x1026e06e0 ins_compl_addleader + 676\n4   nvim                          \t       0x1025d498c insert_execute + 2796\n5   nvim                          \t       0x1028b4ba0 state_enter + 144\n6   nvim                          \t       0x1025d649c insert_enter + 3236\n7   nvim                          \t       0x1025d3e78 edit + 396\n8   nvim                          \t       0x1027b7020 op_change + 548\n9   nvim                          \t       0x1027bba18 do_pending_operator + 5196\n10  nvim                          \t       0x1027a2ed4 normal_execute + 9284\n11  nvim                          \t       0x1028b4ba0 state_enter + 144\n12  nvim                          \t       0x102731324 main + 17544\n13  dyld                          \t       0x18a31fe00 start + 6992\n```\n\n\n\nmaybe related:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/21330",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Seems like after a `c` operation enters insert mode, typing a character triggers `ins_compl_addleader`, which calls `ins_compl_newleader`.  At that point the completion list is either not yet initialized or was just cleared, so `ins_compl_next` walks into a null pointer.   I tried several cases but couldn't reproduce this crash. Is `autocomplete` enabled, or is there some other completion plugin?",
